# JamShield application Kconfig (sourced automatically by the Zephyr build).

config JS_ESPNOW
	bool "Enable ESP-NOW tertiary bearer"
	default n
	help
	  Compile the ESP-NOW shim against the Espressif HAL (esp_now.h /
	  esp_wifi.h) exposed by the Zephyr ESP32 port. Zephyr has no native
	  ESP-NOW L2, so this depends on those HAL headers being available in
	  the build. When disabled, espnow_l2.c builds as a logging stub and the
	  bearer manager treats ESP-NOW as unavailable, keeping the WiFi+BLE
	  failover path fully functional. See PRD.md Section 7.3.

config JS_SENSOR_DHT11
	bool "Use DHT11 (temperature + humidity) instead of the LDR"
	default y
	help
	  Read a DHT11 on GPIO4 (digital 1-wire) instead of the LDR on GPIO34
	  (analog ADC). Both can stay wired on their separate pins; this switch
	  only chooses which the sensor thread reads. Set to n to use the LDR.

source "Kconfig.zephyr"
